articles.post_title: A healthy diet is for health
articles.post_body: Access to nutritious food is critical to health and resilience. Food is Medicine is a concept that reaffirms this connection, recognizing that access to high-quality nourishment is essential for well-being.
articles.author: Selvarasu

articles.post_body: A healthy, balanced diet gives your body nutrients. Nutrients are like fuel for your body. They give you energy. And they keep your heart beating, your brain active, and your muscles working.
articles.author: Vijaykumar

articles.post_body: Traditional medicine comprises medical aspects of traditional knowledge that developed over generations within the folk beliefs of various societies, including indigenous peoples, before the era of modern medicine.
articles.author: Ranjithkumar

articles.post_title: The rich history of traditional medicine in India
articles.post_body: India has a rich history of traditional systems of medicine based upon six systems, out of which Ayurveda stands to be the most ancient, most widely accepted, practiced, and flourishing indigenous system of medicine. The other allied systems of medicine in India are Unani, Siddha, Homeopathy, Yoga, and Naturopathy.
articles.author: Selvarasu

articles.post_title: Oldest system of medicine in southern India
articles.post_body: Siddha medicine is a form of traditional medicine originating in southern India. It is one of the oldest systems of medicine in India. In rural India, siddhars have learned methods traditionally through master-disciple relationships to become local "healers" known as siddhars.
articles.author: Sheikabdulla

articles.post_body: Ayurveda or Ayurvedic medicine is a system of traditional medicine native to India, which uses a range of treatments, including panchakarma ('5 actions'), yoga, massage, acupuncture, and herbal medicine, to encourage health and wellbeing.
articles.author: Ranjithkumar
